ice of Advancement at Chicago Office of Advancement at Peoria Office of Advancement at Rockford Office of Advancement at Urbana University of Illinois Foundation  Search for:    Blueprint Home / Education / MD Student Services and Support / Student Experience / Blueprint  Blueprint tlowery1 2019-10-11T13:21:07-05:00 Advising Service Blueprint The overall goals of the overall student advising project are to: understand the end-to-end student experience from admission through matching and graduation; identify barriers to and facilitators of an integrated advising experience for a student’s academic, career, and personal well-being needs; propose strategies that are likely to enhance the student advising experience working largely within existing College of Medicine resources. The advising service blueprint helps to visualize that student experience as it plays out over four years. Click a section below to enlarge. Education MD Admissions Requirements and Timeline Application Process Tuition and Financial Aid Campus Selection Curricular Programs Interview Day Student Life FAQs Contact MD Curriculum and Academics Physician Competency Reference Curricular Programs Assessment and Evaluation Scholarly and Research Opportunities Visiting Student Information DME Resources MD Student Services and Support Student Affairs Student Experience Blueprint Specialty Webinars Specialty Resource Directory MSPE MSPE Quartile in Class Calculation (2021 Graduates and forward) MSPE Quartile in Class Calculation (2019 and 2020 Graduates) Registrar Student Financial Aid and Debt Management Student Honors and Awards MD Student Life Diversity Ceremonies and Events University Medical Student Council (USMC) Educational Environment Director of Medical Student Learning Environment Reporting Mistreatment or Concerns College Policy & Guidelines Positive Learning Environment Policy Teacher & Student Guidelines Examples of Negative Behaviors DMSLE Notes Educational Affairs Curricular Innovations Natio